# Deploy to Vercel after every push to main

## Rule

After pushing to `main`, **always deploy to production**. Do not consider work done until the deploy succeeds.

## How to deploy

```bash
vercel --token $VERCEL_TOKEN --prod --scope $VERCEL_SCOPE --yes
```

The token and scope are in `.env.local` (`VERCEL_TOKEN` and `VERCEL_SCOPE`).

If the Vercel CLI is not installed:
```bash
npm install -g vercel
```

## After deploying

1. Verify the production URL returns the expected content (not a 404 or old version)
2. Only then is the task complete

## Cron job limits

Vercel Hobby plan only allows **one run per day** per cron. Do not set cron schedules more frequent than daily (e.g. no `*/15 * * * *`). The deploy will fail if any cron runs more than once per day.

## Do NOT

- Say "pushed to main, it will deploy automatically" — it won't unless Vercel auto-deploy is configured
- Leave it to the user to deploy
- Consider the task done before verifying production